name: Northridge at Babcock Ranch
description:
ABOUT THE HOME ENERGY RATING SCALE
The HERS (Home Energy Rating System) Index allows buyers to compare the relative energy efficiency of different homes. The HERS Index home energy rating is determined by an independent RESNET-certified home energy rater ("Rater"). The lower a home’s score, the more energy efficient it is in comparison to the HERS referenced home. For every one-point decrease in the HERS Index score, there is a corresponding one percent (1%) reduction in energy consumption as compared to a home with a HERS Index of 100. A home with a HERS score of 100 reflects a home built to 2006 IEEC Building Codes. See the bottom of this page for more information on HERS scores.

amenities.name: Northridge located
amenities.description: Northridge is located in Babcock Ranch, the first solar panel town in the Country. 75 MW of clean energy, for a combined total of 150 MW capacity and 687,000 solar panels.

amenities.name: Close Neighborhood
amenities.description: Close to the Neighborhood Lake Timber Lodge and Cypress Lodge. Convenient locations that both offer a gathering room, catering kitchen, dual-sided fireplace, zero-entry pool, and BBQ grills.

amenities.name: Square Footage
amenities.description: Close to Founder's Square, including Babcock restaurants, The Lake House, Slater's Goods & Provisions, Square Scoops Creamery, Splash Pad, The Hatchery business incubation center, event lawn with band shell, kayak and canoe launch, and boardwalk.

amenities.name: Quick access
amenities.description: Quick access to WellWay, a full-service health club that offers childcare, 6-lane saltwater pool, workout equipment and free-weight room, pilates & cardio studio fitness classes, massage therapist, and Lee Health occupational & physical therapy. Enjoy fitness classes - from yoga to boot camp classes. Fitness activities provided for every WellWay member.

amenities.name: Enjoy fitness
amenities.description: Enjoy fitness classes - from yoga to boot camp classes. Fitness activities provided for every WellWay member.

amenities.name: Square Footage
amenities.description: B-Street Plaza will offer an array of dining, retail, commercial, and office spaces located south of Founder's Square.

amenities.name: miles Crescent
amenities.description: 2.5 miles from Crescent B Commons offering Taco Tuesdays and DJ nights at M’Xuma. Pizza and Karaoke nights at Pi Local. Pet Supermarket, The Royal Paw Grooming and The Animal Hospital at Babcock. Great Clips, Fiore & Ela Salon and Clover Nails for your beauty needs. Kumon Learning Center offering additional education. Fifth Third Bank and so much more at Crescent B Commons.

amenities.name: Home Designs
amenities.description: 2.5 miles to The Shoppes at Yellow Pine featuring a Marshalls, Ace Hardware, Aesthetics Lounge & Spa, Boujee Nail Bar, Carvel Ice Cream, Five Below, Five Guys, Fountain Pools, HomeGoods, Hope Chiropractic, Jersey Mike’s, Marshalls, Oar & Iron Raw Bar & Grill, Panera Bread, Papa Johns, Seymour Orthodontics, TGH Urgent Care, TGH Medical Center, Ulta Beauty, Verizon, and Yummy Express. Enjoy outdoor dining and gathering areas overlooking Sunset Lake.

amenities.name: minutes Edison
amenities.description: 25 minutes to Edison Mall, including a wide variety of department and sporting goods stores, and Edison Park movie theater.

amenities.name: Home Designs
amenities.description: Less than 8 miles to Publix Super Market at The Shops at Verandah. 20 minutes to The Forum shopping plaza, including Target, Home Depot, Bed Bath & Beyond, Petco, and more.

amenities.name: minutes Fort
amenities.description: 25 minutes to Fort Myers River District, offering restaurants, boutique shops, and tons of events and attractions. 25 minutes to Edison Mall, including a wide variety of department and sporting goods stores, and Edison Park movie theater.

amenities.name: Square Footage
amenities.description: Bullhorn Park and Sunset Park conveniently located just outside of Founders Square providing walking paths along with over 40 miles of community, recreation and greenway walking trails throughout Babcock Ranch.

amenities.name: Approximately 17,000
amenities.description: Approximately 17,000 acres, with 50% dedicated to greenways, playgrounds, community gardens, fishing dock and dog parks.

amenities.name: Jack Peeples
amenities.description: Jack Peeples Park featuring six tennis courts, four pickleball courts, a full basketball court, and two bocce ball courts, soccer field and playground.

amenities.name: New! Curry
amenities.description: New! Curry Creek Linear Parks in Midtown featuring Blue Bird Park, Hillcrest Park, The Lagoon, Explorers Park, Bark Park and Palmetto Park.

amenities.name: Newly ground
amenities.description: Newly ground breaking William & Mary Ann Smith Sports Complex, featuring turf baseball and softball fields, football field with track, soccer field and Skate Park.

amenities.name: Near William
amenities.description: Near William and Mary Ann Smith Sports Complex, a regional park and outdoor sports facility offering a trailhead to Bill Hammond Trails, the sports complex will offer football, softball, baseball and multipurpose fields, a skate park, game night field, running track, expansive flex lawns and ample parking.

amenities.name: Become member
amenities.description: Become a member of the Parks & Recreation Program that offers open gym access, various camps, amenity rentals and special members only events.

amenities.name: Natural gas
amenities.description: Natural gas community with 322 homesites.

amenities.name: Water preserve
amenities.description: Water and preserve view homesites.

amenities.name: Stories
amenities.description: Life Tested®, consumer-inspired and innovative 1- and 2-story home designs.

amenities.name: Smart home
amenities.description: Smart home technology.

amenities.name: New town
amenities.description: New town of 19,500 homes and 6 million sq. ft. of commercial space.

amenities.name: Nearby Bloom
amenities.description: Nearby Bloom Academy providing childcare and Babcock K-12 Neighborhood Charter Schools with onsite campus.

amenities.name: Live life
amenities.description: Live the life at Babcock Ranch, the 1st solar powered city in America.

amenities.name: Florida Green
amenities.description: Florida Green Building Coalition (FGBC) 2023 Builder of the Year for the most certified single-family homes.

homesites.name: 42497 Cascade Drive
homesites.overview:
ABOUT THE HOME ENERGY RATING SCALE
The HERS (Home Energy Rating System) Index allows buyers to compare the relative energy efficiency of different homes. The HERS Index home energy rating is determined by an independent RESNET-certified home energy rater ("Rater"). The lower a home’s score, the more energy efficient it is in comparison to the HERS referenced home. For every one-point decrease in the HERS Index score, there is a corresponding one percent (1%) reduction in energy consumption as compared to a home with a HERS Index of 100. A home with a HERS score of 100 reflects a home built to 2006 IEEC Building Codes. See the bottom of this page for more information on HERS scores.
